    "description": "AstraZeneca India South Asia Partners is actively seeking a talented and motivated Radiologist to join our dynamic team in Visakhapatnam. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout AstraZeneca India South Asia Partners:\nAstraZeneca India South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBA from a recognized university\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n• Proficiency in NABH Standards\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Visakhapatnam, Andhra Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with AstraZeneca India South Asia Partners!",
